SIMPLE: ides
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ides
<hw>Ides</hw> <pr>(⟦imac⟧dz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>idus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>ides</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anc. Rom.
Calendar)</fld> <def>The fifteenth day of March, May, July, and October,
and the thirteenth day of the other months.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>ides</qex> of March remember.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Eight days in each month often pass by this name, but
only one strictly receives it, the others being called respectively the
day before the <xex>ides</xex>, and so on, backward, to the eighth from
the <xex>ides</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Idio-</ent>⟦br⟧
